Is API Key Free?

Short answer: Usually no.

OpenAI does not provide a permanent free API quota. API usage is billed separately from ChatGPT subscriptions.

| Question                   | Answer                         |
| -------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| API Key creation           | ✅ Free                         |
| Using API                  | 💲 Paid (pay for usage)        |
| Credit Card Required       | Usually yes, to enable billing |
| ChatGPT Plus includes API? | ❌ No                           |
| ChatGPT Go includes API?   | ❌ No                           |
| API Billing Separate?      | ✅ Yes                          |


=====

Free Amount

| Item                     | Current Status                                                   |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Create Account           | Free                                                             |
| Create API Key           | Free                                                             |
| Free Monthly API Credits | ❌ Generally none for new accounts                                |
| Usage Without Billing    | Usually not possible beyond any promotional credits (if offered) |


If OpenAI runs a temporary promotion, your account may receive trial credits, but you should not rely on this because it changes over time.
========

Billing Example

| Usage            | Cost                                 |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| 100 requests     | Depends on the model and token usage |
| 1,000 requests   | Depends on the model and prompt size |
| 1 million tokens | Depends on the selected model        |


API pricing is based on tokens, not on the number of questions alone.

